@nalind You're right, I missed that. The existing "Cross Compile" task uses `go tool dist list` which already includes `linux/riscv64`. So compilation is already validated on every PR.

The remaining gap would be release binaries and Docker images, but following the same logic as Podman (distro packages are the distribution path), that may not be needed here either.

Happy to close this if you think the current cross-compile coverage is sufficient.
